&lt;p&gt;This is a tutorial for making figures that are common in microbial ecology. Here I’m using data and code from my publication in Geobiolgy. You can fork the repo by clicking the button above!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Once you have the data downloaded, you’ll need to set up your environment. This code depends on the R packages being loaded here:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre class=&#34;r&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;#load libraries 
pacman::p_load(tidyverse)&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Next, read the data into a dataframe. You can preview the data in the table below this code chunk.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre class=&#34;r&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;#read the data into a dataframe
data &amp;lt;- read_delim(&amp;quot;https://raw.githubusercontent.com/CaitlinCasar/Casar2020_DeMMO_MineralHostedBiofilms/master/orig_data/DeMMO136_Dec2015toApril2018_noChimera_otuTable_withTaxa_d10000.txt&amp;quot;, delim=&amp;quot;\t&amp;quot;, comment = &amp;quot;# &amp;quot;)&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
